{
  "answer": "**In Manusmṛti (Laws of Manu) 1.31, the cosmogonic claim is that the Self-Existent One (Svayambhu) caused the four social orders (*varṇas*)—the Brahmin from his mouth, the Kshatriya from his arms, the Vaiśya from his thighs, and the Śūdra from his feet—to emanate from his body for the prosperity of the worlds.**[^1]\n\nThis forms part of the broader creation account in chapter 1, where the divine entity sequentially produces the elements, senses, gods, time, and social structure from himself.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Manusmṛti, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/01/translation/#p-13a2db).\n\n[^2]: Manusmṛti, Chapter 1, [chapter](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/01/translation/).",
